NoUI Platform

**Unified Defect Taxonomy**

**& Metrics Reference**

Layer 5 of 5: Defect Management System

DERP Proof of Concept

Version 1.0 --- February 2026

Document Status: Draft for Review

1\. Purpose

This document is the single authoritative reference for the defect
classification vocabulary and metrics definitions used across the entire
five-layer defect management system. Every defect record, dashboard
display, alert, report, and metric in Layers 1 through 4 draws its
terminology and definitions from this document.

Maintaining a single taxonomy prevents the drift that occurs when
different teams or documents invent their own severity labels, category
names, or metric definitions. In pension administration, where a "High"
severity defect has specific fiduciary implications, consistent language
is not a convenience---it is a compliance requirement.

1.1 How to Use This Document

-   **When classifying a new defect:** Use the Category definitions
    (Section 2), Severity definitions (Section 3), and Scope definitions
    (Section 4), then derive Priority from the matrix (Section 5).

-   **When reading a dashboard or report:** Reference this document for
    the precise meaning of any classification term or metric.

-   **When a defect doesn't fit:** Follow the Taxonomy Evolution process
    (Section 8) to propose a new category or modification.

-   **When onboarding a new team member or agency:** This document
    serves as the training reference for the defect management
    vocabulary.

