3.1 Severity Determination Rules

-   **When in doubt, classify higher.** Downgrading a severity is a
    documented decision requiring justification. Upgrading never
    requires justification.

-   **Any demo case failure is automatically CRITICAL.** The demo cases
    are hand-calculated from statute. If one fails, a fundamental rule
    or calculation is wrong.

-   **Any eligibility determination error is CRITICAL.** Telling a
    member they are or aren't eligible for retirement is a life-altering
    communication. Getting it wrong is not a "High."

-   **Severity is about the defect, not the fix.** A one-line code
    change can fix a CRITICAL defect. The ease of the fix does not
    affect the severity of the defect.

